STUDENT HANDBOOK - KEY POLICIES

ACADEMIC POLICIES

Attendance Policy:
- Students must maintain 80% attendance rate
- More than 3 absences per month may lead to warning
- Excused absences require medical certificate or parent's letter
- Tardiness of more than 15 minutes counts as absence

Grading System:
- Quarterly Grade: Class Participation (20%) + Quizzes (30%) + Exams (50%)
- Final Grade: Average of 4 quarterly grades
- Passing Grade: 75% (General Average)
- Academic Excellence: 90% and above with no grade below 85%
- Dean's Lister: Top 10% of the batch

Academic Probation:
- Grade below 75% in any major subject
- Two consecutive failing grades
- Must attend tutorial sessions
- Cannot join extracurricular activities

DISCIPLINARY POLICIES

Dress Code:
- Proper school uniform daily
- White polo shirt with school logo
- Black pants/skirt (proper length)
- Black leather shoes (clean)
- ID must be worn at all times

Prohibited Items:
- Weapons of any kind
- Alcohol and illegal drugs
- Gambling materials
- Electronic devices during class hours
- Expensive jewelry and accessories

Sanctions:
- First Offense: Warning and guidance counseling
- Second Offense: Parent conference and community service
- Third Offense: Suspension (3-5 days)
- Serious Offense: Expulsion (due process observed)

CAMPUS POLICIES

Library Usage:
- Open Monday-Friday 7AM-6PM, Saturday 8AM-12PM
- Maximum 3 books borrowed at a time
- Overdue fine: ₱5 per book per day
- Lost books: Replacement cost + 50% surcharge

Computer Laboratory:
- Login with student ID required
- No food and drinks inside
- Save files in USB, not in lab computers
- Report any technical issues immediately

Sports Facilities:
- Proper sports attire required
- Facilities reservation through PE Department
- Equipment must be returned after use
- Injuries must be reported immediately

FINANCIAL POLICIES

Tuition Fees:
- Payment modes: Full, Semi-annual, Quarterly, Monthly
- 5% discount for full payment
- Due dates: 1st week of month/quarter
- Late payment fine: 2% per month

Refund Policy:
- 100% refund before classes start
- 50% refund within first week
- No refund after first week
- Processing fee: ₱200

Scholarships:
- Academic Scholarship: 90-95% (25% discount), 96-100% (50% discount)
- Athletic Scholarship: Varsity players (30% discount)
- Financial Assistance: Based on family income

STUDENT SERVICES

Guidance and Counseling:
- Academic counseling
- Career guidance
- Personal counseling
- Peer counseling program

Health Services:
- School clinic: Monday-Friday 8AM-5PM
- Annual medical check-up required
- Emergency medical assistance
- Health education programs

Transportation:
- School bus service available
- Student discount on public transport
- Parking area for private vehicles
- Bicycle racks available

